<item>
            <title>[PPLNS-7737] Configure AWS Key/Secret rotation for the Callminer BulkAPI storage target</title>
                <link>https://theverygroup.atlassian.net/browse/PPLNS-7737</link>
                <project id="20015" key="PPLNS">Data Enablement</project>
                    <description>&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name="Description"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Description&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Callminer BulkAPI export jobs will push files to &lt;/p&gt;
{env}
&lt;p&gt;-lakehouse-holding-zone. To do this we need to create and maintain a storage target object on the TVG Callminer account. The storage target will contain the details needed for the push to the holding zone bucket, including the AWS Access Key and Secret Key for a Callminer service user on the AWS account.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For security reasons, the Access and Secret keys will need to be stored in AWS Secrets Manager with automated expiry and rotation. A lambda function will be responsible for creating and updating the storage target on the TVG Callminer account with the latest keys.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This task is to add a Callminer service account to the platforms service account configuration (which will handle the rotation of the keys) and create a lambda function to update storage target on the TVG Callminer account each time the keys are rotated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Platforms service account configuration repo =&amp;gt;&lt;a href="https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/platform/user-access/service-accounts" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/platform/user-access/service-accounts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example key rotation lambda (Brick FTP) that can be used for reference =&amp;gt; &lt;a href="https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/platform/user-access/service-accounts/-/blob/master/src/brick_ext_server_key_manager/lambda_function.py?ref_type=heads" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/platform/user-access/service-accounts/-/blob/master/src/brick_ext_server_key_manager/lambda_function.py?ref_type=heads&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name="APIRequestDetails"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;API Request Details&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The storage target can be created and updated on the TVG Callminer account by sending a POST (create) or PUT (update) request to the Callminer API;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;POST /api/storagetargets&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Host:&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://apiuk.callminer.net/bulkexport" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;em&gt;https://apiuk.callminer.net/bulkexport&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Authorization: Bearer abc1234&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Content-Type: application/json;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;charset=utf-8&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is an example JSON payload to set a storage target;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"&gt;&lt;div class="preformattedContent panelContent"&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[
  {
    "AccessKey": "12345",
    "SecretKey": "67890",
    "Region": "us-east-1",
    "Bucket": "Example Bucket",
    "BaseFolder": "FolderName",
    "Name": "AWS Storage Example",
    "Type": "AwsS3"
   }
]&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For a PUT request, add &lt;/p&gt;
{storageTargetName}
&lt;p&gt; to the API route (the name that has been previously set for the storage target).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The request will need a bearer token for authorization. This is obtained by a POST request to the authorization API prior to the request to the BulkAPI. An example of an authorization request is shown below;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;POST connect/token&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Host:&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://idpuk.callminer.net" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;em&gt;https://idpuk.callminer.net&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Json payload;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"&gt;&lt;div class="preformattedContent panelContent"&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;{
  "client_id": "abcd-1234",
  "client_secret": "abcd-1234",
  "grant_type": "client_credentials",
  "scope": "https://callminer.net/auth/platform-bulkexport"
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
